claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table comparing recombinant vaccine versus standard-dose vaccine across primary and secondary outcomes (PCR-confirmed influenza A and B, hospitalizations for influenza, pneumonia, cardiorespiratory events), showing number of cases per 1,000, unadjusted rate ratios, adjusted hazard ratios, relative vaccine effectiveness percentages, and P values. does not support the claim because the table provides clinical effectiveness and outcome data without any information on antigenic match to WHO- or FDA-selected influenza strains.
